{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_2goncharova_ver03/data/sn83045462/00280605153/1948111601/0332.xml":{"full_text":"New Tax, Price Laws\nCalled All-Important\nTo Economic System\nDemocrats Will Be Held\nResponsible for Actions\nLeading to Any Recession\nBy David Lawrence\nThe Democratic Party has ac\nquired a tremendous responsibility\nas a result of the last election. The\nDemocrats have taken the credit\nfor the high farm income and for\nthe high wages. They cannot now\nallow the levels of farm Income or\nwages to drop. These factors are\nInseparably interwoven with the\neconomic future of the United States\nand also with its national politics.\nFor the voters in the next con\ngressional elections will hold the\nDemocratic Party responsible if any\nrecession or depression has occurred.\nTo avoid any recession or depres\nsion, the administration must make\nthe present economic system func\ntion efficiently. It cannot tinker\nwith the machinery or put Into effect\nsuch restrictions as will \"kill the\ngoose that lays the golden eggs.\u201d\nThe fact of the matter is that the\nadministration is irrevocably com\nmitted to maintain the inflationary\n\"prosperity\u201d or to try to level it off,\nbut it cannot permit any serious de\nflation to occur unless it wishes to\nlose both Houses of Congress in 1950.\nThe Republican Party, which had\nbeen worried about the economic\nfuture during the four years ahead\u2014\nand there were many comments that\nGov. Dewey, if elected, would have\nhad a difficult time preventing a\nrecession\u2014is now breathing a sigh\nof relief and saying that perhaps\nit is just as well that the Democrats\nare to undertake the most difficult\nJob in a century\u2014to prevent a\ndepression under present circum\nstances.\nRecessions Not Inevitable.\nDepressions and recessions are not\ninevitable. There is no reason why\neconomic factors should be allowed\nto get out of hand in a nation in\nwhich economic facts are as widely\npublicized as they are in America.\nThe danger lies solely in the\nmanner in which attempts are made\nto prevent the growth of inflation.\nThis can lead precipitately to a\nserious deflation. There are certain\nfacts, of course, about the economic\nfuture which no administration can\ninfluence.\nThus there is the matter of arma\nment. In order to prepare America\nagainst a possible war with Russia,\nbillions of dollars are being spent\nfor armament and billions are being\nsent to Europe under the Marshall\nPlan. If there should be peace with\nRussia or a lessening of the tension\nand a reduction of the armament\nexpenditure or if the harvests in\nother countries of the world should\nproduce a surplus of farm products,\nthus depressing prices in the United\nStates, an adjustment of some kind\nWill become necessary.\nThese are many businesses in the\nUnited States which at the moment\nare not enjoying \"prosperity\u201d due to\nbalancing of supply and demand and\nto readjustments forced on them\neither by high costs or their in\nability to compete efficiently with\nplants built by larger competitors in\ntimes when construction costs were\nmuch lower than they are today.\nWhen some of the labor leaders lump\ntogether all the profits of industry:\nand generalize from such a result,'\nthey are overlooking the smaller\nbusiness units in which the rate of\nprofit happens to be low.\nCould Cause Deflation.\nThe Idea of an excess-profits tax\nhas been suggested as one means of\nreaching the larger companies but\nunfortunately nobody has been able\nto devise an excess-profits law that\nwas ever applied fairly to smaller\nbusinesses or to those which hap\npened to be in the growth stage\nwhen the excess-profits tax was im\nposed. Examination of the experi\nence with World War I and World\nWar II excess-profits-tax laws shows\nthat they invariably helped the\nlarger business by permitting them\nto pay a lower per cent over-all in\ntaxes than was paid by their smaller\ncompetitors. In this way, it may be\nsaid that the excess-profits laws\nhave hurt competition and have\ndiscriminated in favor of the larger\nbusinesses.\nIt was easy enough for President\nTruman on the stump during the\ncampaign to call for an excess\nprofits tax, but he may see an excess\nprofits law putting out of business\nmany smaller concerns which will\nfind the equity markets closed to\nthem because the outlook for a fair\nreturn on the investment will be\nconsiderably dimmed for those who\nare asked to invest risk capital.\nSimilarly, the large companies may\nfind It necessary to abandon ex\npansion of facilities because pros\npective dividends will be less. This,\nIn turn, could cause a deflation in\nthe heavy-goods Industries and bring\non unemployment.\nFor these reasons, the manner\nand method of imposing taxes and\nthe manner and method of con\ntrolling prices are all-important.\nWhen the Democratic Party in the\nnext Congress really comes face to\nface with its responsibility, there\nwill be less and less talk of radical\nand extreme legislation and more\nz talk about how to maintain the pres\nent prosperity.\n(Reproduction Rlshts Reserved 1\nFRIDAYS 6 F. M.\nWASHINGTON AUTO AUCTION\nuit e\u00bbt\u00abi\u00bbiit\u00ab u. liiw i\u00bbti\u00bbi-\nThis Changing World\n\u2018Direct Approach\u2019 Move by Evatt and Lie\nFor \u2018Big Four\u2019 Parley Expected to Fail\nBy Constantine Brown\nReports from Key West, where\nPresident Truman Is vacationing,\nsay that the \u201cdirect approach\" en\ngineered by Dr. Herbert Evatt, pre&i\ndent or tne u.\nN. General As\nsembly, and\nTrygve Lie, sec\nretary general of\nthe U. N., for\nImmediate B1 g\nFour conversa\ntions outside the\nUnited Nations\nwill be declined\npolitely.\nThe tempor\nary White House\nin Florida is In\nfrequent contact\nwith Secretary\nof State Mar\nConatantlne Brawn.\nshall in Paris and Mr. Truman has\nleft him a complete free hand to\ndeal with the situation in whatevei\nmanner he wishes. Prom the re\nports reaching Key West it appears\nthat Gen. Marshall and his advisers\nhave reached the conclusion that\nMessrs. Evatt and Lie have acted\nsolely on an \u201cinspiration from Mos\ncow.\u201d The Western representatives\nin Paris are particularly surprised\nat Mr. Evatt\u2019s attitude. In the past\nhe has been shouting bloody murder\nevery time the big powers attempted\nto reach decisions over the head of\nthe smaller nations whose chief\nprotagonist was the Australian rep\nresentative.\nThe representatives of the West\nern powers involved in the Berlin\ncontroversy consider the proposition\nof the two high officials as \"churn\ning butter to make butter.\"\nNo Change in Situation.\nThere has been no change what\nsoever in the general situation. The\nWestern delegates admit that it is\na threat to the peace and security of\nthe world, but they also feel that\nthey have left no stone unturned to\nobtain a satisfactory solution. The\nprincipal handicap has been Rus\nsia's attitude. The Kremlin, after\ngiving the impression last summer\nof agreeing to lift the blockade,\ninstructed Marshal Sokolovsky to\nblock the agreement by the well\nknown Soviet tactics. The result\nwas that no agreement was reached,\nalthough the Western powers were\nmore than anxious to see that prob\nlem solved in order to proceed with\nconversations leading to peace with\nGermany.\nSo long as the Berlin blockade is\nmaintained by the Soviet govern\nment there can be no direct con\nversations with Moscow on that sub\nject, in the (pinion of Gen. Marshall\nand his Western colleagues. The\nmatter was referred to the U. N.,\nwhere a group of six neutrals have\ntaken it up to offer a solution. And,\ninsofar as the Western powers are\nconcerned, it will remain in the\nhands of that international or\nganization which was created by all\nthe \"peace-loving nations\u201d\u2014includ\ning the U. S. S. R.\u2014for the purpose\nof solving such disputes. The \u25a0\u2018United\nStates and the overwhelming ma\njority of the U. N. members do not\nintend to go over the head of that\norganization in matters as critical\nas those which have resulted from\nthe illegal blockade imposed by the\nRussians.\nRoad-Block to Peace.\nAmerican and other Western dip\nlomats are reported to have pointed\nout to Messrs. Evatt and Lie that\ntheir appeal should have been di\nrected to Prime Minister Stalin and\nthe Politburo alone rather than the\nother interested powers, since it was\nthe Kremlin which ordered the\nblockade which has become the\nroad-block to peace. America, Brit\nain and Prance made far-reach\ning concessions to the Soviet\npoint of view last August to obtain\nonly a face saving agreement for\nthemselves. They cannot go any\nfurther until the Soviet government\norders lifting of the controls from\nsurface communication between the\nWestern zones and Berlin. If Mos\ncow is really interested in improving\npresent world conditions it can do\nit in the easiest manner by an\nnouncing that the controls have\nbeen lifted and actually doing so.\nIt is up to the policy framers in the\nKremlin to show their good will and\nreal Interest in peace.\nNew direct conversations either at\nthe level of heads of state or for\neign ministers, as suggested by the\n\u2018\u2018voices of Moscow\u201d here and abroad,\ncan only increase the present con\nfusion without adding anything to\nward improvement of the threaten\ning situation in Europe.\nThis point of view of the Ameri\ncan delegation in Paris has been\nconveyed clearly to President Tru\nman in long dispatches which are\nsaid to have been fully indorsed by\nthe Chief Executive, who since his\nre-election has much more of a free\nhand than in the past and sees as\nclearly as his representatives in\nParis that the Soviet is attempting\nto maneuver the United States into\na policy of appeasement without of\nfering anything tangible for the\npeace of the world.\nClear-Cut Issues\nParty7 Leaders Confident on Votes\nTo Make Congress Follow Truman Line\nBy Doris Fleeson\nDemocrats interested in organiz\ning the 81st Congress in a manner\nwhich will aflord maximum support\nto President Truman are satisfied\nthat the votes\nare there to do\nit.\nSpurring them\nto a supreme ef\nfort is the mem\nory of the 79th\nCongress, osten\nsibly Democrat\ncontrolled, i n\nwhich committee\ncoalitions of Re\npublicans and\nconservative\nD e mocrats,\nmostly Southern\ne r s, effectively\nburied the Tru\nDorl> FlMion.\nman program and ran me sessions\nto suit themselves.\nAccording to studies now being\nmade, a repetition of this situation\ncan be avoided if the President and\nhis leaders act boldly from the start.\nThe take-off is up to them as the\npleaders \"suggest\u201d to caucuses of\nSenate and House Democrats who\nshall be on the party committees\n\u25a0which in turn recommend the per\nmanent committee assignments. j\nAre There Enough Votes?\nWith the tactical moves firmly, in\nthe hands of the leadership the\nnext question is: Are there enough1\nvotes in the caucuses themselves to\nsupport the leaders in proposals to\nexile Progressive Senator Taylor\nand the Dlxiecrats and to pack the\ncommittees with Truman Demo\ncrats? Those who say yes, argue as\nfollows:\nThe new Senate majority is 54.\nLess Senator Taylor and Dixiecrat\nj Senator Eastland, whose exile is\n'now being debated in both White\nHouse and Congressional quarters,\nit is 52. Senators Taylor and East\nland are at opposite poles in every\nparticular so their votes always\nwould cancel one another. They\ncould not in fact affect the Truman\nmajority either in caucus or on the1\nfloor.\nOf the remaining 52, the South\nerners can probably count on 21; the\nNew Dealers figure they have 25 sure\nj votes and that pressure from the\nWhite House could bring in most\nof the rest.\nThe new House includes 263.Dem\nocrats, 171 Republicans and onej\nAmerican Labor party, the Democra\ntic edge being 92.\nThe new members total 116 of\nwhom 101 are Democrats. Of this:\n101, 75 replaced Republicans, which;\nmeans that they had to come from\noutside the South and are in all!\nFLOOR M=s\nL. T. FOLK\n4632 Wise. Ava. WO. 0521\nQuality Always And\nMore Tea per Bag\n\"SALAD!'\nTEA-BAGS\nlikelihood liberal. Anyway, as North\nerners or Westerners, it will be to\ntheir interest to support the Presi\ndent, as he campaigned on issues\nappealing to their constituencies.\nThe Southern States send 105\nRepresentatives to the House, so\nthey are, in any case, a minority.\nHiey were in a minority to a lesser\nextent in the 79th Congress which\nhad a majority of 239 Democrats.\nBut alio they were more largely\nprotected by seniority and the\nHouse New Dealers had dwindled\nto a rather rudderless group which\nhad little confidence in the Tru\nman leadership.\nTurning to Left Seen.\nThat has changed. In the opin\nion of those who worked with the\ncongressional campaign committee,\nmost of the newcomers are vigorous\nliberals who, added to the New Deal\nveterans, will be a clear majority.\nThe middle-roaders, it is argued,\nwill turn left with the vote-getting\nPresident. Enough Southerners\nhave been retired, it is said, to cut\ndown their seniority privileges ma\nterially, especially if the 11 Dixie\ncrats are disciplined.\nThe President is reported to be\nin a forgiving mood. But the word\nis that some people are not to be\nforgiven and the President has\nproved in the past to be a good\nhater. It probably also is not dif\nficult for him to recall his unhappy\nyears of '45 and '46 when, though\nostensibly he led a congressional\nmajority, the Republocrats frus\ntrated all his designs.\nIn his campaign, Vice President-,\nelect Barkley flatly refused at any\npoint to appease the South; he\nwould not even do an \"I\u2019m South\nerner myself\u201d act anywhere he\nwent. Speaker-prospective Ray\nbum, who did unnumbered chores j\nfor the President, complained about j\nthe so-and-sos who \u2019\u2019ought to leave!\nour party.\u201d\nWhether they will now suit the:\naction to the word is the question\nnow being debated in party coun\ncils. Those who think they should,\nsee it as a clear-cut issue of party\nresponsibility.\nTHE NUMBER fOR\nLUMBER\nphone NA. 1348\nGLAZED WINDOWS\nAND SASH\nBarker Lumber Co.\n649 N.YAv.N.W.\u00ab1523 7thSt.N.W.\nLOUIE\n\u2014By Harry Hanan\nLa_\nfn- m\nOn the Other Hand\nGranddaddy of Scientific Polls,\nOr a Slow Train Through Indiana\nBy Lowell Mellett\nIt\u2019s about time we stopped kidding\nthe pollsters. About time we began\nlending a helping hand to that little\nband of beleaguered scientists. They\nhave said they\nintend to try to\nfind out where\nthey went wrong\non the election\nin order that\nthey may never\nmislead us again.\nAnd we can be\nsure they mean\nto do just that.\nAside from the\nfact that it is\ntoo good a busi\nness to give up,\nthey really be\nlieve in what\nthey do and sin\nLowtl! Mellctt.\ncerely desire to serve us.\nSo, for one, I propose to offer\na little assistance and will present\nhere an experience they may find\nuseful as a case study. This is rather\ngenerous on my part, since the\npollsters gave nobody better reason\nfor kicking himself in the pants\nthan they gave me. For nobody had\nbetter reason to be skeptical of polls\nthan I had. I probably conducted\nthe first scientific poll in history, as\nI will relate in a moment.\nNot only that, but I\u2019ve been guess\ning elections\u2014sometimes correctly\u2014\never since 1896. I only missed on\nthat first one because Mark Hanna\ngot the factory owners to say they\nwould close their plants if McKinley\nwasn't elected. As it was I lost a\npair of B. and B. skates and should\nhave learned a lesson.\nKnew Enough of Factors.\nThis year I knew enough of the\nfactors to enable me to forecast a\nTruman victory. I knew that the\nlabor leaders, after their earlier in\ndecision, had really gone to work\nfor the President and were using\nall the know-how they had picked\nup in \u201940 and \u201944.1 knew the farmers\nhad had their teeth jarred by Har\nold Stassen\u2019s pronouncement, seem\ningly on Gov. Dewey s behalf, con\ncerning farm price supports. I knew\nwhat the veterans were saying pri\nvately, whether Justly or not, re\ngarding Gov. Dewey\u2019s draft defer\nment. I knew that Mr. Truman had\nthe best of the issues, machine\nmade for him by the 80th Congress.\nAbove all, I even knew that truth is\nmighty and will prevail. But\u2014\nI' also knew what the poll-takers\nwere reporting. So I discounted all\nelse I knew and fell in line with\nthe other prophets now so utterly\nwithout honor in their own country.\nSince I\u2019m perfectly capable of dis\ntrusting my own Judgment again\nI four years from now', I'd like for the\npollsters to be right. Which brings\nI me to the case study mentioned\nabove.\nIn 1908 William Jennings Bryan\nwas making his third bid for the\npresidency. William Howard Taft\nat theTsft\n2,006\nmuiMin\nrooms at\nsontibio\nratos all\nwith radio,\nmany with\nTELEVISION\nY MOTH\n7th Avt.\ntf 50fh St.\nNEW YORK\nTIME SQUARE AT RADIO CITY\nmm AND MHO h\u00bbt-.\nIs the time to\nreplace your old\nHEATING EQUIPMENT\nTake it easy this winter with a brand new\nFluid Heat Oil Burner. Set the thermostat\nand your heating worries are over! Fluid\nHeat is clean, efficient heat, too! Winter is\nalmost here so call L. P. Steuart A Bro.,\nInc. today. Easy terms.\nEXTRA\nFuel Oil Tanks\nInstalled on ene-da- no\ntice. Protect yourself\nagainst fuel ell emergen\ncies. Budget Payments!\nwas the Republican candidate. I\nwas a bright young reporter on the\nIndianapolis News. One day, as the\nelection drew near, i went to the\nmanaging editor with a suggestion,\nsomething I\u2019d thought up all by my\nself. It was that he puo a reporter\non a train that ran from South\nBend, up on the northern border,\nto Evansville, way down in the\nsouthwest pocket of the State, and\nhave him interview every passenger\nthat got aboard. There was such a\ntrain, I'd ascertained, a local or ac\ncommodation train, that left at day\nbreak and didn\u2019t arrive till dark. It\ndidn\u2019t pass up a single whistle stop\nas it chugged from North to South\nand East to West in a complete\ncriss-cross of the State.\nResult Only Thing Wrung.\nNot one to overlook a brilliant\nidea, the managing editor told me\nto tootle up to South Bend and take\nthat peripatetic poll myself. It\nturned out to be a sounder under\ntaking than I had foreseen. Posi\ntively scientific. Once the train got\ngoing I found I had the heart and\nmind of Indiana right at the end\nof my pencil. The passengers rep\nresented every trade and profession.\nFarmer*, carpenters, salesmen, law\nyers, bankers and so on. All Hoosiers\nand all local folks. None traveling\nvery far, mostly Just from one sta\ntion to the next. A constantly\nchanging passenger list, only the\ntrain crew going all the way.\nI interviewed them, each and all,\nand put down their answers. And\nby the time that train reached\nEvansville there was no need to\nproceed with the election. Bryan\nwas in by a landslide.\nNow that was a scientific poll. A\ngeographical cross-section and a\npopulation cross-section of the\nState.\nThe only thing wrong was the\nresult. Taft carried Indiana by 10,\n771 votes.\n(Copyright 1848, Oloba Syndicate.)\nPOINTING\nBrick and Stone Wells\nGuaranteed Against\nWater Penetration\nASHINQTON\nATERPROOFINQ\nSOI U. Coitol SL\nMl. 9454\nATERLESS Products\nMcLemore\u2014\nFinds Jealous Birds\nGet More Fish\nBy Henry McLemore\nGIFU, Japan.\u2014More about eormo\nrant fishing in Gifu, Japan, the\nworld\u2019s center of this business.\nTo train a cormorant to fish\nfrom a boat\ntakes the pa\ntience of a Jap\nanese Job. Three\nyears is the\nminimum time\nIt takes to teach\na Cormorant to\nget accustomed\nto his harness\nand his master,\nthe great glow\nof the flrebasket\nwhich provides\nhim light for\nnight Ashing,\nand the excite\nment of the\nHenry HcLemore.\nother birds working so close to him.\nWhen the birds are captured at\nthe age of 15 or 16 months they\nare, of course, naturally adept at\nswimming, fishing and diving. But\nthe aforementioned things must be\ntaught by the usho (master fisher\nman) who owns them. Cormorants\nare usually good for 12 or 13 years'\nservice, and some still working in\nthe Nagara-gawa River here are\nmore than 24 years old.\nKeeps Them Hungry.\nAn usho fishes a dozen birds at\na time. He handles the leashes at\ntached to the cormorants with much\nmore skill than any puppeteer ever\ndisplayed. He never allows the\nlines to get tangled, no matter in\nhow many directions the birds dive\nand criss-cross each other in search\nof fish. He never looks at the\nbirds, but trusts to \u201cfeel\u201d alone.\nBy adjusting the tightness of the\nloop of the cord which fits about\nthe bird\u2019s neck, the usho can con\ntrol how many fish and what size\nfish the bird can get into his stom\nach. Early in the run down the\nriver the loop is adjusted so that\nthe birds can get a fair amount\ninto their stomachs unless they have\nbeen fed during the day and still\nhave food in them. As the fishing\ngoes on, the usho, using his eyes for\nscales, weighs the birds and tightens\nthe loop of those who are filling up\nin order to keep them hungry\nenough to continue fishing. Should\na bird become lackadaisical, his\nloop is loosened so that he can get\nmore to eat and gain pep.\nWhen a bird has filled his throat;\nMUB80K\nsa/mn\nDAILY WONTS\n/n\nMxrmtwtu\nULOUUU...\nlit much utitaf\nCONSULT TOUt\nTVAVIl AMNT\nCOLONIAL AIRLINES I\nCAU EXECUTIVE TOII J\nULCERS-COLITIS\nACID STOMACH\ndue to hyperacidity can be quickly relieved\nby a revolutionary DRUQLE88 preparation\nknown at V M. Pure vegetable matter\ncompounded In tablet form Easy and\npleasant to take No drugs of any kind\nProvides stomaeb and connecting Intestine!\nwith protective lining of vegetable mudn.\ncoating over Inflamed surfaces and pro\ntecting them against excess stomach adds\nand irritating food roughages, thus giving\nInflammations a chance to heal. Leading\ndoctors and hospitals hare announced\namaxlns results from this preparation,\nwhich was heretofore told only on morti\ncian's prescription Now on sale here\nCome In today for a bottle of 100 tablets.\nPrice. S3 00 on Iron-clad money-back\nguarantee. Trial else for only $1.00.\nVITA FOOD STORES\nM3 Hth St. N.W. SOM 14th St. N.W.\nBETWEEN EBPCO. \u00ab>80\nwith the proper number of fish (the\nusho tells this by feel, too) he is\npulled in and made to disgorge his\ncatch by a squeeze of the throat.\nFight for Record Catch.\nAs we pointed out in yesterday\u2019s\nstory, cormorants are tremendously\njealous. They fight to outdo one\nanother in the amount of fish\nbrought in. They make all manner\nof noises when, for one reason or an\nother, the usho puts them on the\nsidelines (a big, roomy basket) and\nsends in a reserve cormorant. Cor\nmorants are about the size of a big\nmallard duck\u2014and can they travel\nunder water! Going downstream\nthey are like a streak, and fast as\nthe small Jap trout is, it can\u2019t es\ncape a hustling cormorant. The\nbirds usually have 8 to 14 fish in\ntheir throats when pulled to tha\nboat for disgorging. A top-notch\ncormorant will catch from 100 to\n200 fish a night.\nThere is no such thing as buying\na well-trained cormorant from an\nusho. Once he has trained tha\nbird it becomes a part of his fam\nily. While we were here as high as\n75.000 yen were offered for a bird,\nbut the would-be buyer left empty\nhanded. The fishing doesn\u2019t pay as\nit did before the war, when a great\ndeal of the catch was purchased for\nthe royal household. But to tha\nushos and their sons, their profes\nsion is almost a religion. It has\nbeen going on for some 1,700 years,\nand the ushos say it will go on for\never.\n(Distrloutcd by MeNausht Syndicate, lne.)\nORIENTAL RUG\nSALE\nSAVE VP TO 50%\nThese are the lowest prices in 5 years!\nBeautify your home with these lovely rugs\nthat ore made to withstand the hardest serv\nice don't scold your children buy\nthem Oriental rugs and let them play to\ntheir heart's content.\nA FEW OF THESE SPLENDID VALUES:\nKERMANSHAH SAROUK\n10x15 were $1295. NOW $895 9x12 were $550. NOW $369\n10x17 were M95. NOW 975 10x18 were 1295. NOW 895\n10x19 were 1795. NOW 1195 10x14 were 995. NOW 695\nAlso 200 selected pieces from\n2x3 to 12x20 from $12.50 up\nSANITARY\nRUG CLIANING CO.\n118 C Street N.W. District 0356\ndheid the HA!RE\nte the TORTOISE..\nWhy should I race home to do laundry?\nArcade-Sunshine will call for my bundle,\nwash and finish each piece carefully and\ncorrectly. Next laundry day, just dial\nRAndotph 8000\nARCADE-SUNSHINE\n\"Comp/#fa Quoting\"\nBring your Ford 4n now for our\nFord winter service on easy terms. It's\nFord-planned service designed to keep\nyour car running smoothly and economically\nall winter. Like all Ford Dealer Service it\u2019s\ntops, with savings from:\n1. Genuine Ford Parts\n2. Ford-trained Mechanics\n3. Factory-approved Methods\nSpecial Ford Equipment V\nllitan t* tka Frad Alla* Draw,\nSunday Ivaniaf*\u2014NIC natwark.\nUalan la Ika Fard Tkaatar, Friday\n\u25a0vaninyi\u2014CIS natwark. Saa yavr\naawtyayar far lima and alalia*.\nr Then's no place\nlike HOME i\ns ftr tod Service 1\n^Zj*jtoerkun\nFord dealers know Fords best!","height":"31776","width":"22484"}}
